race.comment: ARTISTRY IN MOTION (1) was trending the right way before dropping back to 1200m of the Belgravia Stakes where he was well beaten as a 60-1 chance. He looks better suited coming back to this grade following a strong run in Open 3YO company two back. Can cross to the lead and bounce back to winning ways. ESTA MIRANDO (7) won impressively first-up at this course before getting a long way back and never really getting into the race in a CL3 at Belmont last time out. The inside draw can see her sit much closer today and the winkers go on. Can bounce back with Pike remaining in the saddle. PONY UP (8) box seated and landed the knockout blow at Belmont 15 days ago, running away to win impressively. The map looks a little sticky for her, but she's shown plenty of class and with improvement expected, she'll be hard to hold out. SUPER SUNNY (3) was solid from the front last time out and is not out of this.
